Node.Notes: Uncertain. In parallel text in is36:5, it is 1st sg "I said."
Because of different perspective (here 1st person vs. 2nd person in is36:5), interpreted as S-P (whereas P-S in is36:5).
Tree assumes deriding direct portrayal "You [seem to] say: Only words of lips [is] strategy and strength for war."
Most either read absolute state or omit officer. Tree allows for possibility that strange phrase refers to an under-official of even the least of the Assyrian king’s servants.
